Characters are well done, and in this I mean that you'll find things you like and dislike about them...I've known people to give up on the series because they hated all the characters. Personally I think it makes them more real. The story is a little confusing at first, and I think purposefully vague in parts. You definitely should watch the movie after the series (End of Evangelion, Death and Rebirth is more of a recap than anything new, since the new part is repeated in EoE). <br>
<br>
I also echo, this series, and especially the movie, have disturbing parts of them (in one way or another). If you're younger (which I somewhat doubt if you're talking about buying a box set), or are subject to the opinions of your parents influencing you, you might want to hold off on it for now. While there's certainly nothing beyond an R rating here (especially in the series), there is a lot of strange happenings, strange visuals (and gore), and pseudo-Christian religious symoblism. If that'd offend your parents (or you), perhaps leading to bans on anime or something...that'd be bad. If that's not a concern, then forget I mentioned it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
