ings <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  and it depends on whether it's the series or the movie. Both have implied and sorta shown romantic tension/relationship type stuff between 14 year olds (the children are all 14) and adults. Evas aren't mechs, they're creatures in armor (this is shown in like episode 2, so it's not really a spoiler)...so you get some strange behavior from that, and things that wouldn't happen if it were simply a machine. Primarily it's religious symbolism that's a little weird. The whole plot winds up revolving around it (plus the enemies are called angels, the main computers are the magi, etc). From what I've read, nobody that worked on the series was a Christian (or spinoff religion), they just borrowed elements from it that they thought were cool or whatever. So you get this odd mix of supposed Dead Sea Scroll prophecy and half-biblical references (like the Lance of Loginous...which was supposedly the spear the pierced Christ...aka Spear of Destiny).  Anyway, if you can put aside any knee-jerk reactions to religious type references like that (it doesn't say anything about Christ or whatever) then you should be fine. Sorta like how the Matrix had references to things, but Eva has more. Actually, in part, knowing some of the references might increase enjoyment <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
You've also got your past suicides, masturbation (movie), and acid trip imagery near the end of it all. Without telling you the end, I can't really explain how truly strange it is...but trust me...it's freaking on crack (especially the movie). The last couple episodes are weird, but seemed to confuse or piss people off more than weird them out. The series has a big theme of realizing and coming to terms with yourself, and the last couple of episodes boil down to that, using primarily reused animation....<br>
<br>
There are some other things, but (I think) that's about it in general.  I guess the thing that makes Eva stand out as disturbing is that the whole plot involves stuff like that. Contrasted to other series that might have a couple weird episodes or scenes...<br>
