<br>
e.g.<br>
Over zealous observer: Your use of blues must be refering to your sense of loss over your father.<br>
<br>
Artist: Actually I was never that close to my father.  I just used the blues cause I thought they were pretty.<br>
<br>
With Evangelion, I believe this is not so much the case.  While I don't think it was made to be analyzed all day long, I think they tried to make it so you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>could</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> do that.  So many things in Evangelion represent something else, that it's hard (for me at least) to tell when something is being used as deliberate imagery, or when it's to be taken at face value.<br>
<br>
With that being said, I highly recommend it (it's my favorite anime series).<br>
<br>
As far as the &quot;offensive&quot; scenes.  They don't get particularly explicit, and none of it is without purpose.  It's not something I'd recomend watching with parents.  Most American adults think of cartoons as being for kids, so when they get sexual (nothing shown, but stuff is heard) it's a  little akward.  Slight gore factor, and as mentioned, none of the gore is present just for the sake of having gore.<br>
<br>
Evangelion, as far as I know, has never appeared on American television.  It's ok for Japanese primetime, but too much for the American censors.  And the story was supposed to come to an end with the last episode.  However the creator (can't remember his name right now) got a bunch of angry letters, some of them death threats, about how gyped they felt about the ending, that they demanded a different ending.  So he made the movies, which were basically a big f*ck you to all the fans...everyone gets what they wanted, but in the most f*cked up way possible (hence why the movies end up being something that would be rated R instead of PG-13).  I think he even showed some of the death threats in the movie (I was told...cause I can't read<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyanidedreamer>Cyanidedreamer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(4/23/03 3:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2341.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:Re...</span><hr size=1> Evangalion should be made a psycological study for psycolagy students as there is a lot to be decifred and looked at deeper,<br>
